<h2>Why Mouth Breathers Lose Sleep Quality</h2>
<p>Mouth breathing during sleep creates a cascade of problems: dry mouth, reduced oxygen intake, snoring that wakes your partner, and poor sleep architecture. The problem is especially acute for people with tongue posture issues or nasal resistance. Many sleepers aren't even aware they're breathing through their mouth until they wake up parched.</p>
